Call for Research: Ethical AI Community


Issued: July 15, 2026


The Ethical AI Community invites rigorous academic contributions to our inaugural quarterly publication. 
Our mission is to steward AI development toward human flourishing and sustainable economic health.


Primary Research Topics


• Defining Ethical AI: Frameworks for moral alignment and stewardship.

• Impacts of Unethical Development: Systematic risks to security and trust.

• Beneficiaries: Who benefits when AI is aligned with human interests?

• The Implication of Immoral/Amoral AI: Long-term consequences for society, community cohesion,
and global economic stability.

The Academic Gate: Submission Protocol

    To ensure academic rigor, we operate on a quarterly Academic Gate protocol: Submission Window: Last week of March, June, September, December. Publication Window: First week of the subsequent quarter.

